solution: ```class Solution:
    def brokenCalc(self, startValue: int, target: int) -> int:
        ops = 0
        while target > startValue:
            if target & 1:
                target += 1
            else:
                target //= 2
            ops += 1
        return ops + (startValue - target)
```
efficiency: HIGH
time complexity: O(log target)
space complexity: O(1)
energy implications: LOW
explanation: Work backwards from target to startValue. If target is odd, increment once to make it even; if even, halve it. Each step reduces target exponentially, yielding logarithmic time. When target ≤ startValue, only subtractions remain.

